  3. Usage
  --------
    If you start the program with /h or /? as argument you will get a brief
    help about the available options.
    Options can be given preceded by / or -
    Lower and upper case letters mean the same.
    Multiple options can be given in a line. Each group of options must start
    with a / or - and must not contain spaces. The groups must be separated
    by one or more spaces. The /s, /f and /c options must be last ones in a
    group, the best is to give them separately.

    Options are:

    /h , /?       shows this help screen
    /v            DOS version
    /e            list of environment variables
    /k            settings of DOS-switches ( BREAK, VERIFY )
    /d            current date
    /t            current time
    /m            free conventional memory
    /g            graphic driver and current mode
    /s[drive]     total space on drive
    /f[drive]     free space on drive
    /c[drive]     current directory on drive
    /a            size information about all hard drives

    If you use /s, /f or /c without a drive letter, the current drive will be
    selected.
    If no option is given, DOSINFO uses "/vdtkgmc /a".
    If you specify a filename, the output will be generated in this file,
    not on the screen. The default extension is .TXT
    Note: If given, the name of the output file must preceed all other options.

    Examples:
      DOSINFO             info about everything except environment variables
      DOSINFO /?          get help
      DOSINFO report -dT  current date and time in REPORT.TXT
      DOSINFO /MS /f -c   free memory, current directory, total space and free
                            space on current drive
      DOSINFO /SA /FA     total space and free space on drive A:
      DOSINFO hd.lst /A   total space and free space on all hard drives in
                            the file HD.LST

